menu "breadboard: OTA strategy"

choice BB_OTA_STRATEGY
    prompt "OTA update strategy (/api/update/apply owner)"
    default BB_OTA_STRATEGY_PULL
    help
        Selects which component owns POST /api/update/apply. Exactly one
        strategy is active per board, so /apply has a single registrant and
        bb_ota_pull / bb_ota_boot never both auto-register the route.

        This choice only drives the default of the per-component autoregister
        symbols (BB_OTA_PULL_AUTOREGISTER, BB_OTA_BOOT_AUTOREGISTER); each can
        still be overridden to register the route manually.

config BB_OTA_STRATEGY_PULL
    bool "In-place pull (bb_ota_pull owns /api/update/apply)"
    help
        bb_ota_pull downloads + flashes the new image in place at runtime
        heap, then reboots. Suitable for boards with enough contiguous heap
        for the TLS + OTA buffers.

config BB_OTA_STRATEGY_BOOT
    bool "Boot-mode full-heap pull (bb_ota_boot owns /api/update/apply)"
    help
        bb_ota_boot arms a one-shot flag and reboots; the manifest resolve +
        firmware download run at FULL early-boot heap before any subsystem
        starts. For tight / serial-less single-core boards (e.g.
        esp32-s2-mini) that cannot afford an in-place pull under a fragmented
        runtime heap.

config BB_OTA_STRATEGY_NONE
    bool "None / push-only (no /api/update/apply owner)"
    help
        Neither pull nor boot auto-registers /api/update/apply. Use for
        push-only firmware delivery (POST /api/update/push) or boards with no
        onboard OTA trigger.

endchoice

config BB_OTA_STATIC_STACK
    bool "Use static (BSS) stacks for OTA PULL-strategy worker tasks"
    default n
    help
        Reserve the OTA PULL-strategy worker task stacks (ota_pull, upd_check)
        in static BSS at boot instead of allocating them from the heap on demand.
        Enable on boards where high-uptime internal-heap fragmentation can make
        those workers fail to spawn. Consumers enable it per-fleet (e.g.
        TaipanMiner sets it in sdkconfig.defaults).

        Boot-mode boards (BB_OTA_STRATEGY_BOOT) self-exempt via their
        AUTOREGISTER=n; this option affects only the two PULL-strategy runtime
        workers.

endmenu
